.TH "FBB::columnWidth" "3bobcat" "2005-2006" "libbobcat1-dev_1\&.10\&.0-x\&.tar\&.gz" "Object Manipulator"

.PP 
.SH "NAME"
FBB::columnWidth \- Manipulator class enforcing column specific Table column widths
.PP 
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fB#include <bobcat/columnwidth>\fP
.br 
Linking option: \fI-lbobcat\fP 
.PP 
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
An object of this class may be immediately inserted into an
\fBstd::ostream\fP to insert a \fBFBB::Table\fP whose columns are as wide as
necessary to fit their widest elements\&.
.PP 
.SH "NAMESPACE"
\fBFBB\fP
.br 
All constructors, members, operators and manipulators, mentioned in this
man-page, are defined in the namespace \fBFBB\fP\&.
.PP 
.SH "INHERITS FROM"
-
.PP 
.SH "CONSTRUCTORS"
.IP o 
\fBcolumnWidth(FBB::Table &table)\fP:
.br 
The normal use of this constructor is within a insertion
expression\&. 
.IP o 
\fBcolumnWidth(columnWidth const &other) throw()\fP:
.br 
The standard copy constructor is available, but is normally not used\&.

.PP 
.SH "MEMBER FUNCTIONS"
There are no publicly available memberfunctions\&.
.PP 
.SH "OVERLOADED OPERATORS"
.IP o 
\fBstd::ostream &::operator<<(std::ostream &str, 
FBB::columnWidth const &ew)\fP:
.br 
Tables may be inserted into \fIstd::ostream\fP objects using this
overloaded operator, which sets the column width to
\fBFBB::TableSpec::ColumnWidth\fP prior to inserting the table into the stream\&.
.IP 
Note that this operator is not defined in the namespace \fBFBB\fP\&.
The overloaded assignment operator is available, but is normally not
used\&. 
.PP 
.SH "EXAMPLE"
See \fBtable\fP(3bobcat)
.PP 
